# Keep the build context to what the image actually needs: go.mod, go.sum, and
# the Go sources. Everything below either busts the layer cache or has no
# business in a build context.

# Every checkout produces a different .git — packfiles, refs, FETCH_HEAD — so
# leaving it in the context invalidates `COPY . .` and the compile behind it on
# every single CI run, which makes the GitHub Actions layer cache useless and
# actively harmful: each run then writes a fresh full layer set into a shared,
# size-capped cache, evicting entries that would have helped.
.git
.gitignore

# Not used by the build, and changing a workflow should not force a recompile.
.github

# Private key material. Not a leak in the published image, since only the
# compiled binary is copied out of the builder stage — but a local `make image`
# would otherwise bake a developer's real keys into an intermediate layer that
# lingers in the layer cache.
certs

# Build and test artefacts.
coverage.out
ocsp-responder

# Documentation and local orchestration: editing a README should not invalidate
# the compile.
*.md
docker-compose*.yaml
.env
.env.example
examples
scripts
